✅ 1. Install Required Plugins
From Jenkins Dashboard (as shown in your screenshot):
Click "Manage Jenkins"
Click "Plugin Manager"
Go to "Available" tab (or "Installed" if already added)
Search and install:
✅ Git plugin
✅ Maven Integration plugin
✅ Publish Over SSH plugin
📌 Restart Jenkins after installing if prompted.

✅ 2. Configure SSH Server (Ansible server)
Go to: Manage Jenkins → Configure System
Scroll down to Publish over SSH
Click Add → configure like this:
Name: ansible-server
Hostname: (e.g., public IP of ansible server)
Username: ubuntu
Remote Directory: /home/ubuntu/maven

Check ✅ Use password authentication, or use a different key

Add Private Key (copy-paste your .pem or use Jenkins credentials)

Save the config

✅ 3. Create a New Job
Click “New Item”
Enter job name (e.g., maven-project)
Select Freestyle project
Click OK

✅ 4. Configure the Job
🔹 Source Code Management
Select Git
Repository URL: https://github.com/PoojithaGowda10/maven-project.git
Branch: */main

🔹 Build
Add Invoke top-level Maven targets
Goals: clean package

🔹 Post-build Actions
Add → Send build artifacts over SSH
Name: ansible-server
Source files: target/*.war
Remove prefix: target/
Remote directory: /home/ubuntu/maven
Check ✅ Exec command if you want to run it after deployment (e.g., restart tomcat)

✅ 5. Build the Project
Click Save
Go to job → Click Build Now
